import pandas as pd
from pyecharts.charts import Map
from pyecharts import options as opts

# ""
df[''] = df[''].apply(lambda x: x + '' if not x.endswith('') else x)

# 
count_area = df[''].value_counts().reset_index()
count_area.columns = ['', '']

# 
pair = list(zip(count_area[''], count_area['']))

# 
map_beijing = Map(init_opts=opts.InitOpts(
    theme='light',  # 
    width='800px',
    height='400px'
))

map_beijing.add(
    series_name='', 
    data_pair=pair, 
    maptype="", 
    is_map_symbol_show=False
)

map_beijing.set_series_opts(label_opts=opts.LabelOpts(is_show=False))  # 

map_beijing.set_global_opts(
    title_opts=opts.TitleOpts(title="", pos_left='left', pos_top='top'),  # 
    visualmap_opts=opts.VisualMapOpts(
        max_=count_area[''].max(),  # 
        is_piecewise=True,  # 
        pieces=[
            {"max": count_area[''].max(), "min": 1000, "label": "1000", "color": "#FF4500"},
            {"max": 999, "min": 500, "label": "500-999", "color": "#FF8C00"},
            {"max": 499, "min": 100, "label": "100-499", "color": "#FFD700"},
            {"max": 99, "min": 0, "label": "0-99", "color": "#FFFF99"}
        ],
        orient='vertical',  # 
        pos_left='left',  # 
        pos_top='middle'  # 
    )
)

#  Notebook 
map_beijing.render_notebook()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import numpy as np
import matplotlib

# 
matplotlib.rcParams['font.family'] = 'SimHei'  #  'Microsoft YaHei'
matplotlib.rcParams['axes.unicode_minus'] = False  # 

# 
cat_cols = ["", "", "", ""]

# 
palette_name = "Oranges_r"

plt.figure(figsize=(18, 12))
for i, col in enumerate(cat_cols, 1):
    plt.subplot(2, 2, i)

    n_categories = df[col].nunique()
    colors = sns.color_palette(palette_name, n_colors=n_categories)

    ax = sns.countplot(y=col, data=df, 
                       order=df[col].value_counts().index,
                       palette=colors)
    
    # 
    total = len(df[col])
    for p in ax.patches:
        count = int(p.get_width())
        percentage = f'{count / total:.1%}'
        ax.annotate(f'{count}\n({percentage})',
                    (p.get_width(), p.get_y() + p.get_height()/2),
                    ha='left', va='center', fontsize=13)
    
    plt.title(f"{col}", fontsize=14)
    plt.xlabel('')
    plt.ylabel('')

plt.tight_layout()
plt.savefig(".jpg", dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')
plt.show()

from matplotlib.patches import Patch

def plot_donut(col, ax):
    value_counts = df[col].value_counts()
    total = value_counts.sum()
    n_categories = len(value_counts)
    colors = sns.color_palette(palette_name, n_colors=n_categories)

    # 
    wedges, _ = ax.pie(
        value_counts,
        startangle=90,
        wedgeprops=dict(width=0.4),
        colors=colors
    )

    # 
    centre_circle = plt.Circle((0, 0), 0.4, fc='white')
    ax.add_artist(centre_circle)

    # 
    legend_elements = []
    for label, value, color in zip(value_counts.index, value_counts.values, colors):
        percent = value / total * 100
        legend_label = f'{label}: {percent:.1f}%'
        legend_elements.append(Patch(facecolor=color, edgecolor='black', label=legend_label))

    # 
    ax.legend(handles=legend_elements, loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5), fontsize=16, frameon=False)

    # 
    ax.set_title(col, fontsize=16)

plt.figure(figsize=(20, 12))  # 
for i, col in enumerate(cat_cols, 1):
    ax = plt.subplot(2, 2, i)
    plot_donut(col, ax)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import folium
from folium.plugins import HeatMap
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd  # geopandas

# 
df_clean = df[['lat', 'lon', '(/)']].dropna()
df_clean = df_clean[
    df_clean['lat'].apply(lambda x: isinstance(x, (int, float))) &
    df_clean['lon'].apply(lambda x: isinstance(x, (int, float))) &
    df_clean['(/)'].apply(lambda x: isinstance(x, (int, float)))
]

# 
heat_data = df_clean.apply(lambda row: [row['lat'], row['lon'], row['(/)']], axis=1).tolist()

gradient = {
    '0.4': '#FFCC99',  # 
    '0.6': '#FF9966',  # 
    '0.8': '#FF6600',  # 
    '1.0': '#CC3300'   # 
}

# 
price_map = folium.Map(location=[39.9042, 116.4074], zoom_start=10)
beijing_boundary = gpd.read_file("beijing_boundary.geojson")

# 
folium.GeoJson(
    beijing_boundary,
    name="",
    style_function=lambda x: {
        "fillColor": "none",  # 
        "color": "black",     # 
        "weight": 2           # 
    }
).add_to(price_map)

# 
HeatMap(
    data=heat_data,
    gradient=gradient,
    radius=13,
    max_zoom=15
).add_to(price_map)

# 
price_map
